{"questionId":"22222569","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>&nbsp;and the value of <em>q</em>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1 </strong></p>\n<p>attempt to form at least one equation, using either&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>5</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>6</mn></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;<em> &nbsp;(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>65</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>25</mn><mi>p</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>q</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>13</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>and&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>96</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>36</mn><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>q</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>16</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;<em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>valid attempt to solve simultaneous linear equations in <em>p </em>and <em>q</em> and by substituting or eliminating one of the variables.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em> <strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If candidate does not explicitly state their values of <em>p</em> and <em>q</em>, but gives&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></math> , award final two marks as <em><strong>A1A0</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to form at least one equation, using either&nbsp;<strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>5</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;</strong>or<strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>6</mn></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em> &nbsp; &nbsp;(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>65</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>26</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>96</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>32</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>valid attempt to solve simultaneous linear equations in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp;by substituting or eliminating one of the variables.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em>&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math>and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If candidate does not explicitly state their values of <em>p</em> and <em>q</em>, do not award the final mark.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22222569","referenceCode":"23N.1.SL.TZ1.4a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of p and the value of q.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}